How about this for a statement of the problem:

Communicants are A and B, spoofer is C.  All messages between A and B
pass through C, who can change them.  A wishes to send a one bit message M
to B without C discovering M.  B and C initially share all information
(anything B knows, C knows).  (Obviously A knows M, while B and C do not.)

	A <-----> C <-----> B

Hal Finney
